FBIS4-10851 "drlat075_l_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 Bolivia Journalists Arrested for Killing U.S. Citizens Journalists Arrested for Killing U.S. Citizens PY1804214694 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 18 Apr 94 PY1804214694 La Paz Television Nacional Network Spanish BFN [Text] Two journalists have been arrested by the Ministry of Government. They have been identified as Edith Munoz and David Garcia, both of whom have been charged with having alleged ties with terrorism. [Begin recording] [Minister of Government German Quiroga] The court investigations are about to be concluded. In keeping with what is established in the law, they were able to see their relatives on 18 April, 24 hours after their arrest, particularly the woman in question. This afternoon the police will be instructed to allow the press access to those arrested and tomorrow they will be placed at the disposal of the courts. We have established that they were very closely involved in the killing of the Mormons, especially the woman. Therefore, we are conducting investigations in this direction. [Unidentified reporter] Do you mean she was more involved than Mr. Garcia? [Quiroga] Yes, absolutely. [Reporter] Are they under suspicion for their involvement in terrorist activities? [Quiroga] Yes. [end recording] That was Minister of Government German Quiroga, who at Government House referred to the arrest of two colleagues.
